normalcy at the border.

1363
01:43:55,766 --> 01:44:01,233
We are now working to restore conditions
to how they were before 2020.

1364
01:44:02,066 --> 01:44:07,833
Slowly but surely, trust, enthusiasm, and
energy will return.

1365
01:44:08,633 --> 01:44:12,466
But of course, it will take some time,
since there’s been a five-year gap.

1366
01:44:14,766 --> 01:44:17,500
Our cooperation isn’t just beneficial,

1367
01:44:17,666 --> 01:44:21,066
it’s also essential for global stability
and prosperity.

1368
01:44:21,200 --> 01:44:25,300
And since the 21st century is Asia’s
century,

1369
01:44:25,900 --> 01:44:29,866
we want India and China to compete in a
healthy and natural way.

1370
01:44:30,300 --> 01:44:34,700
Competition is not a bad thing, but it
should never turn into conflict.

1371
01:44:35,566 --> 01:44:40,933
- The world is worried about a brewing
global war.

1372
01:44:42,033 --> 01:44:47,933
The tensions between China and the United
States in Ukraine,

1373
01:44:48,033 --> 01:44:52,933
Russia, in Europe, in Israel,
the Middle East,

1374
01:44:53,033 --> 01:44:58,233
what can you say about how we in the
twenty first century

1375
01:44:58,433 --> 01:45:00,333
can avoid a global war,

1376
01:45:00,733 --> 01:45:05,166
avoid an escalation towards more conflict,
more war?

1377
01:45:06,833 --> 01:45:12,366
- Look, COVID exposed the limitations of
every nation.

1378
01:45:13,766 --> 01:45:18,300
No matter how much we consider ourselves
as a great nation,

1379
01:45:18,533 --> 01:45:21,033
no matter how progressive
we think we are,

1380
01:45:21,466 --> 01:45:24,533
or how scientifically advanced we believe
we’ve become,

1381
01:45:24,533 --> 01:45:26,866
everyone has their own way of looking at
things,

1382
01:45:27,100 --> 01:45:30,166
in the end, we all found ourselves on the
same ground.

1383
01:45:30,333 --> 01:45:33,233
Every country in the world faced this
reality.

1384
01:45:33,933 --> 01:45:37,133
At that time, it felt like the world would
learn from it.

1385
01:45:39,933 --> 01:45:42,866
That we would move toward a more unified
world.

1386
01:45:44,100 --> 01:45:48,233
Just as a geopolitical order emerged after
World War II,

1387
01:45:49,333 --> 01:45:51,933
many thought something similar would
happen post-COVID.

1388
01:45:52,566 --> 01:45:54,200
But unfortunately,

1389
01:45:54,966 --> 01:45:56,500
instead of

1390
01:46:01,366 --> 01:46:03,733
moving
toward peace,

1391
01:46:04,866 --> 01:46:10,366
the world became even more fragmented,
ushering in a period of uncertainty.

1392
01:46:11,566 --> 01:46:14,166
And the wars have only made it worse.

1393
01:46:16,633 --> 01:46:21,400
I believe that modern wars are no longer

1394
01:46:22,833 --> 01:46:25,433
just about resources or interests.

1395
01:46:29,533 --> 01:46:35,933
Today, I see so many kinds of conflicts
happening.

1396
01:46:37,000 --> 01:46:41,733
Physical battles often get discussed,
struggles are happening in every domain.

1397
01:46:42,733 --> 01:46:47,233
International organizations that were once
powerful have become almost irrelevant,

1398
01:46:47,333 --> 01:46:49,266
no real reforms are happening.

1399
01:46:49,400 --> 01:46:53,133
Institutions like the UN are failing to
fulfill their roles.

1400
01:46:55,433 --> 01:46:56,766
People who

1401
