1453
01:50:52,733 --> 01:50:55,733
Hundreds of Indian passengers were held
hostage.

1454
01:50:56,366 --> 01:51:01,833
It caused massive turmoil across India, as
people faced life-and-death uncertainty.

1455
01:51:02,333 --> 01:51:07,933
Then, in the year 2000, the Red Fort
in Delhi was attacked by terrorists.

1456
01:51:08,400 --> 01:51:12,533
Yet another crisis struck the nation,
intensifying fear and turmoil.

1457
01:51:13,233 --> 01:51:17,033
On September 11, 2001, the Twin Towers
in America

1458
01:51:17,033 --> 01:51:22,233
faced a devastating terror attack,
once again shocking the entire world.

1459
01:51:22,633 --> 01:51:25,433
Because ultimately, the people behind
these attacks

1460
01:51:25,466 --> 01:51:27,233
are driven by a similar
mindset.

1461
01:51:27,700 --> 01:51:32,800
Then, in October 2001, terrorists attacked
the Jammu and Kashmir Assembly.

1462
01:51:33,333 --> 01:51:38,600
Soon after, on December 13, 2001, India’s
Parliament was targeted.

1463
01:51:41,333 --> 01:51:44,333
Within just 8 to 10 months,

1464
01:51:44,533 --> 01:51:49,666
these major
global terrorist attacks took place,

1465
01:51:49,766 --> 01:51:53,633
violent incidents that led to bloodshed
and the loss of innocent lives.

1466
01:51:54,033 --> 01:51:56,233
In such a tense environment,

1467
01:51:56,933 --> 01:52:01,466
even the
smallest spark can ignite unrest.

1468
01:52:01,533 --> 01:52:04,300
The situation had already
become extremely volatile.

1469
01:52:04,933 --> 01:52:10,933
In such times, suddenly,
on October 7, 2001,

1470
01:52:12,766 --> 01:52:17,033
I was given the responsibility of becoming
Chief Minister of Gujarat.

1471
01:52:17,633 --> 01:52:19,800
This was an enormous challenge.

1472
01:52:21,466 --> 01:52:27,866
At that time, Gujarat was recovering from
a devastating earthquake,

1473
01:52:27,933 --> 01:52:33,166
the largest of the previous century, which
had left thousands dead.

1474
01:52:33,633 --> 01:52:39,166
My first major task as Chief Minister was
overseeing the rehabilitation of survivors.

1475
01:52:39,966 --> 01:52:45,200
This was a crucial task, and from day one
after my oath, I immersed myself in it.

1476
01:52:45,733 --> 01:52:50,566
I was a person who had absolutely no prior
experience with government.

1477
01:52:50,933 --> 01:52:53,100
I had never been part of
any administration,

1478
01:52:53,133 --> 01:52:55,133
never even served in government before.

1479
01:52:55,633 --> 01:52:59,500
I had never contested an election, never
even been a State Representative.

1480
01:52:59,700 --> 01:53:02,633
For the first time in my life, I had to
face elections.

1481
01:53:04,666 --> 01:53:11,633
On February 24, 2002, I became a State
Representative,

1482
01:53:12,633 --> 01:53:15,233
an elected representative,
for the first time.

1483
01:53:16,166 --> 01:53:19,900
And it was
only around

1484
01:53:20,333 --> 01:53:24,133
February 24th,
25th, or 26th

1485
01:53:24,333 --> 01:53:27,533
that I stepped into the Gujarat Assembly
for the very first time.

1486
01:53:29,333 --> 01:53:32,633
On February 27, 2002,

1487
01:53:33,233 --> 01:53:37,033
we were seated in
the assembly for the budget session,

1488
01:53:37,533 --> 01:53:39,033
and that same day,

1489
01:53:39,666 --> 01:53:44,233
it had been just three days since I'd
become a State Representative,

1490
01:53:46,066 --> 01:53:49,033
when suddenly, the horrific Godhra
incident occurred.

1491
01:53:49,366 --> 01:53:53,466
It was a tragedy of unimaginable
magnitude, people were burned alive.

1492
01:53:54,133 --> 01:54:00,033
You can imagine, against the backdrop of
incidents like the Kandahar hijacking,

1493
01:54:00,066 --> 01:54:03,966
the attack on Parliament, or even 9/11,

1494
01:54:04,433 --> 01:54:09,633
and then to have so many

1495
01:54:10,000 --> 01:54:13,933
people killed and
burned alive,

1496
01:54:14,733 --> 01:54:18,800
you can imagine how tense and volatile the
situation was.

1497
01:54:20,333 --> 01:54:25,133
Of course, this was tragic for everyone,
everyone prefers peace.

1498
01:54:27,066 --> 01:54:31,733
The perception that these were the biggest
riots ever is actually misinformation.

1499
01:54:32,733 --> 01:54:37,533
If you review the data from before 2002,
you'll see that

1500
01:54:38,133 --> 01:54:43,766
Gujarat faced frequent riots, curfews were
constantly being imposed somewhere.

1501
01:54:43,800 --> 01:54:46,600
Communal violence could erupt over trivial
issues,

1502
01:54:46,633 --> 01:54:50,533
like kite-flying contests or even minor
bicycle collisions.

1503
01:54:51,866 --> 01:54:58,466
Before 2002, Gujarat witnessed over 250
significant riots.

1504
01:55:00,133 --> 01:55:05,733
The riots in 1969 lasted nearly six
months.

1505
01:55:08,233 --> 01:55:13,433
So there was a long history long before I
was in the picture.

1506
01:55:15,633 --> 01:55:19,933
But that one tragic incident in 2002
became a sparking point,

1507
01:55:20,033 --> 01:55:22,933
leading some people towards violence.

1508
01:55:23,233 --> 01:55:28,033
Yet, the judiciary thoroughly investigated
the matter.

1509
01:55:29,033 --> 01:55:35,033
At that time, our political
opponents were in power,

1510
01:55:35,666 --> 01:55:39,466
and naturally, they wanted all allegations
against us to stick.

1511
01:55:40,200 --> 01:55:43,833
Despite their relentless efforts, the
judiciary

1512
01:55:44,233 --> 01:55:47,266
analyzed the situation
meticulously, twice,

1513
01:55:47,300 --> 01:55:50,466
and ultimately, found us completely
innocent.

1514
01:55:50,733 --> 01:55:54,866
Those who were truly responsible have
faced justice from the courts.

1515
01:55:55,666 --> 01:56:00,033
But the most important thing is, in
Gujarat,

1516
01:56:00,566 --> 01:56:06,233
where riots used to happen somewhere or
the other every year.

1517
01:56:07,566 --> 01:56:10,533
But after 2002,

1518
01:56:11,433 --> 01:56:16,433
in 22 years, there hasn’t been a single
major riot in Gujarat.

1519
01:56:16,833 --> 01:56:18,766
Gujarat remains completely peaceful.

1520
01:56:19,333 --> 01:56:24,033
Our approach has always been to avoid
vote-bank politics.

1521
01:56:24,366 --> 01:56:29,400
Instead, our mantra has been: "Together
with everyone, development for all,

1522
01:56:29,433 --> 01:56:32,366
trust from all, and efforts by everyone."

1523
01:56:32,933 --> 01:56:37,433
We’ve shifted away from the politics of
appeasement to the politics of aspiration.

1524
01:56:37,933 --> 01:56:42,366
Because of this, anyone who wishes to
contribute joins us willingly.

1525
01:56:42,733 --> 01:56:48,733
We've continuously strived to turn Gujarat
into a well-developed state,

1526
01:56:49,133 --> 01:56:51,800
and today, Gujarat is actively
contributing toward

1527
01:56:51,833 --> 01:56:53,666
building a developed
India as well.

1528
01:56:55,133 --> 01:56:56,533
- A lot of people love you.

1529
01:56:56,833 --> 01:56:58,566
I've got to hear from a lot of them

1530
