1571
02:00:05,833 --> 02:00:11,033
I don't see enough high effort, deep dive
research,

1572
02:00:11,033 --> 02:00:12,533
I don't know how many books I've read.

1573
02:00:12,566 --> 02:00:17,933
I've read a lot in preparing just to
experience, just to try to understand.

1574
02:00:17,966 --> 02:00:20,433
It requires a lot of preparation, a lot of
work.

1575
02:00:20,466 --> 02:00:23,333
And I would love to see great journalists
do that more.

1576
02:00:23,933 --> 02:00:28,733
And from that place, you can criticize,
from that place,

1577
02:00:28,733 --> 02:00:34,166
you can really investigate the complexity
of a situation of people in power.

1578
02:00:34,733 --> 02:00:38,466
Their strengths, their flaws, the mistakes
they have made,

1579
02:00:38,766 --> 02:00:40,866
but that requires great, great, great
preparation.

1580
02:00:40,933 --> 02:00:45,633
So this, I wish there was more of that, of
great journalism.

1581
02:00:46,233 --> 02:00:52,200
- Yes. Clear, well-directed, and specific
criticism genuinely helps

1582
02:00:52,300 --> 02:00:54,866
