1583
02:00:55,833 --> 02:00:58,666
It leads to a clear-cut policy vision.

1584
02:00:58,800 --> 02:01:02,633
I specifically pay close attention to such
constructive criticism,

1585
02:01:02,766 --> 02:01:05,866
in fact, I actively welcome it.

1586
02:01:06,333 --> 02:01:09,133
Regarding your point about journalistic
headlines,

1587
02:01:10,233 --> 02:01:14,133
if someone’s attracted by catchy headlines
or plays with words,

1588
02:01:14,633 --> 02:01:16,766
I honestly don't mind that much.

1589
02:01:18,266 --> 02:01:21,466
But when there's a deliberate agenda
behind the actions,

1590
02:01:21,733 --> 02:01:23,966
and the truth is deliberately ignored,

1591
02:01:25,233 --> 02:01:29,966
that can cause damage that lasts for
decades.

1592
02:01:30,933 --> 02:01:34,733
If someone focuses on pleasing their
readers

1593
02:01:34,766 --> 02:01:39,033
or viewers with attractive
headlines,

1594
02:01:39,233 --> 02:01:41,933
maybe we can compromise a little.

1595
02:01:42,300 --> 02:01:44,300
But if there's a hidden motive, or if

1596
02:01:44,633 --> 02:01:47,766
things are intentionally twisted to serve
an agenda,

1597
02:01:47,766 --> 02:01:49,933
that's a serious issue worth worrying
about.

1598
02:01:50,333 --> 02:01:53,866
- And in that, the truth suffers, I think.

1599
02:01:54,566 --> 02:02:01,066
- I remember once, in London, I was
invited to give a speech

1600
02:02:02,066 --> 02:02:07,066
at an event organized by a Gujarati
newspaper there.

1601
02:02:07,100 --> 02:02:12,966
So, during my speech, I casually said,
since it was an event attended by journalists

1602
02:02:15,466 --> 02:02:18,066
"What kind of journalism should we have?

1603
02:02:19,833 --> 02:02:22,766
Should it be like a fly or a bee?

1604
02:02:26,066 --> 02:02:31,433
I explained. A fly sits on dirt

1605
02:02:32,733 --> 02:02:34,800
and
spreads the dirt around.

1606
02:02:36,300 --> 02:02:41,966
But a bee lands on flowers, collects
nectar,

1607
02:02:42,166 --> 02:02:45,266
and then shares that
sweetness everywhere.

1608
02:02:46,066 --> 02:02:51,866
Yet, if something wrong occurs, the bee
can sting so powerfully

1609
02:02:51,900 --> 02:02:55,966
that you’d have to hide your face for
three days straight!

1610
02:02:56,666 --> 02:03:01,800
However, some people selectively picked up
just half of my analogy

1611
02:03:02,200 --> 02:03:04,866
and created a huge controversy out of it.

1612
02:03:05,166 --> 02:03:12,066
Honestly, was I being negative about
anyone? Not at all.

1613
02:03:12,066 --> 02:03:14,833
I was simply highlighting the incredible
strength of a bee,

1614
02:03:15,133 --> 02:03:18,200
that even its small
sting can leave such an impact that

1615
02:03:18,866 --> 02:03:23,466
can make someone hide their face for days.
You can't show your face.

1616
02:03:23,866 --> 02:03:26,166
That’s the power journalism should have.

1617
02:03:27,233 --> 02:03:31,766
But unfortunately, some people prefer the
fly approach instead.

1618
02:03:33,900 --> 02:03:36,900
- I now have a new life goal of
becoming the bee

1619
02:03:37,900 --> 02:03:40,166
You mentioned democracy, so—

1620
02:03:40,266 --> 02:03:43,966
And not knowing much about government
until 2002.

1621
02:03:44,666 --> 02:03:50,200
But to—from 2002 to today, you won eight
elections that I could count.

1622
02:03:51,266 --> 02:03:57,366
So, in many of the elections, over 800
million people vote in India.

1623
02:03:59,200 --> 02:04:03,266
What does it take to win an election like
that,

1624
02:04:03,300 --> 02:04:08,566
and to win an election of 1.4
billion people,

1625
02:04:09,366 --> 02:04:16,066
where you get to represent those people in
the biggest democracy in the world?

1626
02:04:17,500 --> 02:04:23,000
- Well, I've been actively involved in
politics for years.

1627
02:04:23,266 --> 02:04:28,300
Before stepping into active politics, my
focus was primarily on organizational work.

1628
02:04:28,866 --> 02:04:32,566
This also included managing elections and
strategizing campaigns.

1629
02:04:33,166 --> 02:04:35,466
So, that was where I dedicated my time.

1630
02:04:36,266 --> 02:04:39,900
For 24 years, the people

1631
02:04:41,166 --> 02:04:47,066
of Gujarat and
India have placed their trust in me

1632
02:04:47,466 --> 02:04:48,700
to lead.

1633
02:04:49,966 --> 02:04:54,266
With unwavering dedication and a deep
sense of duty,

1634
02:04:56,166 --> 02:04:58,933
I try to fulfill the sacred duty

1635
02:05:00,033 --> 02:05:05,466
entrusted to me by the
people I revere as divine.

1636
02:05:06,466 --> 02:05:11,200
I remain committed to honoring their
trust, ensuring it never falters.

1637
02:05:13,666 --> 02:05:16,466
And they see me for what I truly am.

1638
02:05:18,400 --> 02:05:25,266
My government is committed to ensuring
welfare schemes reach every citizen.

1639
02:05:25,900 --> 02:05:29,566
Every scheme must reach its intended
beneficiaries.

1640
02:05:30,266 --> 02:05:34,266
Every beneficiary must be treated equally.

1641
02:05:34,766 --> 02:05:39,100
No one should face discrimination on
caste, creed, faith, wealth, or ideology.

1642
02:05:39,700 --> 02:05:43,366
We must strive to ensure the well-being
and prosperity of everyone.

1643
02:05:44,200 --> 02:05:51,033
This way, even those not directly
benefiting,

1644
02:05:51,166 --> 02:05:54,133
never feel left out or treated
unfairly.

1645
02:05:54,466 --> 02:05:58,166
They find comfort in knowing they, too,
will benefit in due course.

1646
02:05:58,466 --> 02:06:01,066
This fosters a deep sense of trust.

1647
02:06:01,766 --> 02:06:08,300
And trust is the cornerstone of my
governance model.

1648
02:06:09,100 --> 02:06:15,033
Secondly, my governance
flows beyond

1649
02:06:15,566 --> 02:06:17,500
the ebb and flow
of elections.

1650
02:06:18,200 --> 02:06:21,566
My governance is rooted in the people, not
the polls.

1651
02:06:22,366 --> 02:06:29,266
It is committed to the well-being of my
citizens and the greater good of the nation.

1652
02:06:29,533 --> 02:06:34,100
As you may know, I had once set out on a
quest for spiritual awakening.

1653
02:06:34,400 --> 02:06:37,466
So now, I revere my nation as the divine
itself.

1654
02:06:37,666 --> 02:06:41,766
And I now revere the people as a
manifestation of the divine.

1655
02:06:42,766 --> 02:06:44,866
Like a devoted priest,

1656
02:06:45,833 --> 02:06:50,566
my heart is set on
serving the people.

1657
02:06:51,766 --> 02:06:56,966
I don't distance myself from the people. I
live among them, as one of them.

1658
02:06:57,566 --> 02:07:01,666
And I tell everyone I work with, "If you
work hard, I will work harder."

1659
02:07:02,666 --> 02:07:05,066
People see this, and it builds trust.

1660
02:07:05,100 --> 02:07:07,700
Besides, I have no conflicts of interest.

1661
02:07:07,766 --> 02:07:12,466
I have no friends or relatives who stand
to gain from the position I hold.

1662
02:07:13,000 --> 02:07:16,566
The common man appreciates this lack of
vested interest.

1663
02:07:17,200 --> 02:07:19,466
And that's probably just one reason why.

1664
02:07:20,766 --> 02:07:26,200
Moreover, I come from a party with
millions of dedicated volunteers,

1665
02:07:27,266 --> 02:07:32,166
volunteers who are completely devoted to
the welfare of India and its citizens.

1666
02:07:32,433 --> 02:07:35,166
They have had no stake whatsoever in
politics.

1667
02:07:35,466 --> 02:07:39,366
They've held no title, nor strayed where
influence holds sway.

1668
02:07:39,533 --> 02:07:43,300
My party is blessed with millions of
volunteers who work tirelessly.

1669
02:07:43,733 --> 02:07:49,400
I am proud to belong to the world's
largest political party.

1670
02:07:50,266 --> 02:07:53,066
And it's not like my party has been around
forever.

1671
02:07:53,666 --> 02:07:56,400
It reflects the hard work of millions of
volunteers.

1672
02:07:57,466 --> 02:08:02,700
Their selfless service is widely
recognized and valued by the community.

1673
02:08:03,566 --> 02:08:07,566
It fortifies people's trust in the BJP,

1674
02:08:07,766 --> 02:08:10,766
echoed in the election results.

1675
02:08:11,900 --> 02:08:18,066
I never tallied our election triumphs, but
we have had people's blessings.

1676
02:08:18,766 --> 02:08:21,966
- I was wondering if you could speak to
the incredible logistics,

1677
02:08:22,466 --> 02:08:26,066
that blew my mind, of running the
elections in India.

1678
02:08:26,466 --> 02:08:30,100
So, there are a lot of interesting
anecdotes that arise.

1679
02:08:30,766 --> 02:08:33,900
For example, that no voter should be more
than two kilometers

1680
02:08:33,933 --> 02:08:35,366
away from a polling
station.

1681
02:08:35,800 --> 02:08:40,433
The result of that is you have these
stories of voting machines

1682
02:08:40,466 --> 02:08:42,866
having to be
carried to remote regions of India.

1683
02:08:43,166 --> 02:08:47,366
It's really incredible—just every single
voter counts.

1684
02:08:47,600 --> 02:08:54,066
And the machinery of having 600 plus
million people vote—

1685
02:08:55,166 --> 02:08:57,766
Is there some anecdote

1686
02:08:58,400 --> 02:09:02,966
you could speak to
that is particularly impressive to you,

1687
02:09:02,966 --> 02:09:05,666
or maybe you could speak generally to the
logistics of

1688
02:09:05,666 --> 02:09:07,766
what it takes to run an
election that big,

1689
02:09:07,766 --> 02:09:09,166
in a democracy that big?

1690
02:09:10,300 --> 02:09:15,966
- First and foremost, I am truly grateful
for your insightful question.

1691
02:09:16,500 --> 02:09:22,033
Anyone who believes in democracy should
listen to what I am about to share with you.

1692
02:09:23,366 --> 02:09:29,366
We often discuss election results, but all
the behind-the-scenes work is overlooked.

1693
02:09:30,200 --> 02:09:36,300
Let's take the recently concluded 2024
general elections as an example.

1694
02:09:37,300 --> 02:09:42,466
There were 980 million registered voters!

1695
02:09:44,500 --> 02:09:47,500
Each of those voters had a registered ID

1696
02:09:47,600 --> 02:09:53,300
and all the necessary details
in a vast database.

1697
02:09:55,066 --> 02:09:59,500
And this number is twice the entire
population of North America.

1698
02:10:00,900 --> 02:10:04,900
It even surpasses the total population of
the entire European Union.

1699
02:10:06,466 --> 02:10:10,666
Out of the 980 million registered voters,

1700
02:10:11,466 --> 02:10:14,566
646 million people

1701
02:10:15,466 --> 02:10:20,133
ventured out and braved
the intense heat of May,

1702
02:10:20,800 --> 02:10:23,166
determined to
cast their votes.

1703
02:10:23,600 --> 02:10:28,166
Temperatures soared to 40 degrees in some
areas, yet they chose to go!

1704
02:10:29,066 --> 02:10:33,500
And the size of this voter base is double
the population of the United States!

1705
02:10:36,000 --> 02:10:38,966
We had more than a million polling booths.

1706
02:10:39,166 --> 02:10:42,900
Can you fathom all the manpower involved
in this?

1707
02:10:43,866 --> 02:10:49,333
My country has more than 2,500 registered
political parties.

1708
02:10:49,900 --> 02:10:53,666
This staggering figure, with such a vast
array of political parties,

1709
02:10:54,066 --> 02:10:57,100
has the power
to leave the entire world in awe!

1710
02:10:58,066 --> 02:11:04,000
My country has more than 900
round-the-clock news channels.

1711
02:11:06,100 --> 02:11:09,100
There are over 5,000 newspapers published
daily.

1712
02:11:09,700 --> 02:11:13,100
They each play a role in upholding
democracy in their own way.

1713
02:11:13,533 --> 02:11:18,600
Even the humblest villages here

1714
02:11:18,900 --> 02:11:23,500
embrace
technology with remarkable swiftness.

1715
02:11:24,033 --> 02:11:30,233
While some other countries take months to
declare election results,

1716
02:11:30,933 --> 02:11:35,100
we announce the results within a day,
despite the mind-boggling number of voters!

1717
02:11:35,400 --> 02:11:36,733
And you were spot on

1718
02:11:37,466 --> 02:11:40,933
in  saying that even the remotest
villages have polling stations.

1719
02:11:41,466 --> 02:11:44,466
We even use helicopters to transport
polling stations.

1720
02:11:45,200 --> 02:11:48,600
I believe Arunachal Pradesh

1721
02:11:49,466 --> 02:11:52,800
has the
highest-altitude polling booth on record.

1722
02:11:53,333 --> 02:11:57,400
In Gujarat, a polling booth was set up in
the Gir Forest for just one voter

1723
02:11:57,933 --> 02:11:59,400
who was in the middle of nowhere.

1724
02:11:59,600 --> 02:12:01,900
But we ensured a polling booth
was set up for them.

1725
02:12:02,900 --> 02:12:04,900
All I mean to say is that

1726
02:12:08,466 --> 02:12:12,333
we truly leave no stone unturned

1727
02:12:12,500 --> 02:12:16,633
in our unwavering commitment
to strengthening democracy,

1728
02:12:17,900 --> 02:12:22,633
ensuring that we are always fully prepared
and election-ready,

1729
02:12:22,833 --> 02:12:24,800
no matter the
circumstances.

1730
02:12:25,100 --> 02:12:28,766
I firmly believe that India's Election
Commission

1731
02:12:29,166 --> 02:12:32,633
sets a global standard as a benchmark

1732
02:12:33,133 --> 02:12:36,300
for conducting free and fair elections.

1733
02:12:36,933 --> 02:12:38,700
It is the apex decision-maker.

1734
02:12:39,466 --> 02:12:42,166
This in itself is such a remarkable story

1735
02:12:42,333 --> 02:12:46,400
that the world’s top universities should
consider it a case study.

1736
02:12:46,500 --> 02:12:51,600
They should analyze the management behind
it as a valuable learning example.

1737
02:12:52,600 --> 02:12:56,133
Given the sheer number of voters, can you
truly grasp

1738
02:12:56,333 --> 02:12:59,000
the immense depth of political
awareness?

1739
02:12:59,500 --> 02:13:03,000
All of this will make for an excellent
case study

1740
02:13:03,066 --> 02:13:05,400
for the younger generation
worldwide.

1741
02:13:06,533 --> 02:13:09,566
- To me—I love democracy.

1742
02:13:10,200 --> 02:13:13,800
This is one of the main reasons I love the
United States.

1743
02:13:13,833 --> 02:13:17,566
But there's just nothing quite as
beautiful as democracy

1744
02:13:17,600 --> 02:13:19,466
when it functions
in India.

1745
02:13:20,200 --> 02:13:24,900
You know, like you said, 900 million
people registered to vote!

1746
02:13:25,233 --> 02:13:27,766
It really is a case study.

1747
02:13:28,000 --> 02:13:32,600
It's beautiful to see that many people
come together

1748
02:13:32,633 --> 02:13:36,366
willingly, passionately,
casting a vote

1749
02:13:37,133 --> 02:13:41,000
for some person to represent them, like,
they're putting their heart in that.

1750
02:13:41,033 --> 02:13:45,100
It's really important for a person to feel
like their voice is going to be heard.

1751
02:13:45,200 --> 02:13:46,433
It's beautiful.

1752
02:13:46,566 --> 02:13:48,800
Speaking of which, you are loved by a lot
of people.

1753
02:13:48,900 --> 02:13:51,633
You are one of the most powerful humans in
the world.

1754
02:13:51,900 --> 02:13:54,466
Do you sometimes think about whether this
much power

1755
02:13:54,500 --> 02:13:56,300
has a corrupting effect on your
mind,

1756
02:13:58,233 --> 02:14:01,400
especially across the many years that
you've been in power?

1757
02:14:02,900 --> 02:14:08,700
- Well, I don’t think the word "powerful"
quite reflects the journey of my life.

1758
02:14:10,400 --> 02:14:14,000
I can never claim to be powerful,

1759
02:14:14,733 --> 02:14:17,800
for all
I am is a humble servant.

1760
02:14:19,000 --> 02:14:23,100
I even identify myself as not the Prime
Minister, but the Prime Servant.

1761
02:14:23,900 --> 02:14:27,000
And service is the guiding principle of my
work ethic.

1762
02:14:28,800 --> 02:14:33,900
As far as power is concerned, it is
something I have never bothered about.

1763
02:14:35,133 --> 02:14:40,133
I entered politics not to play power
games, but to serve.

1764
02:14:41,000 --> 02:14:44,033
Rather than seeking power,

1765
02:14:44,900 --> 02:14:48,233
I stay committed to doing
and getting work done.

1766
02:14:48,966 --> 02:14:52,000
I am more focused on productivity than
power.

1767
02:14:54,200 --> 02:14:58,200
I have always dedicated myself to serving
the people.

1768
02:14:58,633 --> 02:15:03,366
I have always devoted myself to bringing
about a positive change in their lives.

1769
02:15:04,700 --> 02:15:10,800
- Like you mentioned, you work a lot. You
give your whole soul to your work.

1770
02:15:11,700 --> 02:15:12,900
Do you ever get lonely?

1771
02:15:19,866 --> 02:15:22,800
- Look, I never experience loneliness.

1772
02:15:25,933 --> 02:15:31,600
Because I am an ardent believer in the
philosophy of one plus one.

1773
02:15:33,900 --> 02:15:37,800
And this philosophy of one plus one

1774
02:15:39,300 --> 02:15:44,033
is aligned with my moral compass.

1775
02:15:45,166 --> 02:15:50,600
And whenever I am asked to elaborate on
this outlook,

1776
02:15:51,200 --> 02:15:56,300
I say, "The first one represents Modi, and
the other one represents the Almighty."

1777
02:15:56,766 --> 02:16:00,633
I am never alone, for He is always there
to keep me company.

1778
02:16:01,533 --> 02:16:03,833
This is just how I function.

1779
02:16:04,500 --> 02:16:09,600
Having wholeheartedly embraced the ideals
of Swami Vivekananda,

1780
02:16:12,433 --> 02:16:17,200
I firmly believe that service to mankind
is service to God.

1781
02:16:18,033 --> 02:16:23,533
For me, the nation itself is divine, and
mankind is a reflection of the divine.

1782
02:16:24,700 --> 02:16:30,700
I walk this path with the conviction that
serving the people is serving the divine.

1783
02:16:32,100 --> 02:16:37,033
That’s why the very notion of struggling
with loneliness

1784
02:16:37,233 --> 02:16:40,600
has never even remotely
crossed my mind.

1785
02:16:41,500 --> 02:16:43,300
Like at the time of pandemic.

1786
02:16:50,300 --> 02:16:54,133
With the lockdown and traveling
restrictions in place,

1787
02:16:55,600 --> 02:17:00,100
I came up with a way to make the most of
my time.

1788
02:17:01,533 --> 02:17:03,233
I designed a

1789
02:17:03,733 --> 02:17:07,700
governance model that operated
seamlessly through video conferencing.

1790
02:17:09,166 --> 02:17:15,433
I kept myself occupied with remote work
and virtual meetings.

1791
02:17:16,433 --> 02:17:21,900
Another thing I did was to connect with the
people I had worked with throughout my life.

1792
02:17:22,600 --> 02:17:25,333
Among my party's volunteers nationwide,

1793
02:17:25,533 --> 02:17:28,000
I made a list of those
who were 70 and older.

1794
02:17:29,500 --> 02:17:35,100
Some of the volunteers had very humble
beginnings and came from

1795
02:17:35,833 --> 02:17:37,800
very modest
backgrounds.

1796
02:17:37,900 --> 02:17:41,900
I personally called every volunteer aged
70 and above.

1797
02:17:42,900 --> 02:17:49,100
I made it a point to inquire about their
health and their families' well-being.

1798
02:17:49,500 --> 02:17:52,133
I inquired about how their area was
coping.

1799
02:17:52,700 --> 02:17:55,533
I asked these questions to make sure they
were doing well.

1800
02:17:56,233 --> 02:17:58,566
This allowed me to build rapport with
them,

1801
02:17:58,766 --> 02:18:00,533
and we would go down the memory
lane.

1802
02:18:01,000 --> 02:18:07,466
They were touched that the Prime Minister
would check on them in the pandemic.

1803
02:18:08,333 --> 02:18:12,033
I made around 40 calls every day, without
fail.

1804
02:18:12,700 --> 02:18:15,533
I carried on with this throughout the
pandemic.

1805
02:18:16,200 --> 02:18:20,300
It gave me the chance to reconnect and
relive old memories with familiar faces.

1806
02:18:21,000 --> 02:18:25,900
Loneliness is never a concern for me, as I
always find ways to stay engaged.

1807
02:18:26,833 --> 02:18:29,800
And I have long been at peace with myself.

1808
02:18:30,000 --> 02:18:33,233
The time I spent in the Himalayas have
helped me develop this.

1809
